	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Missing 12-year-old Naledi Zondo has been found, KwaZulu-Natal police said on Saturday. "We are still waiting for more information, but she was found in Durban, and she is alive," said police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala. Naledi disappeared on Monday afternoon and pictures of her in her red and white school uniform were circulated widely, while her mother Nokulunga Zondo hoped for the best. READ: 'I'm going out of my mind' - mother of missing Maritzburg girl Her mother was not immediately available for comment on Saturday morning. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  